  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best side jobs to get on the weekend to earn extra cash?",
  "response": "There are many side jobs you can pursue on weekends to earn extra cash. The best ones for you will depend on your skills, interests, and availability. Here are some popular and effective options:\n\n1. **Freelancing** - Offer your skills on platforms like Upwork, Fiverr, or Freelancer. Common freelance jobs include writing, graphic design, web development, and digital marketing.\n\n2. **Rideshare or Delivery Driver** - Work as a driver for companies like Uber, Lyft, DoorDash, or Instacart. This offers flexibility and can be quite lucrative depending on your location.\n\n3. **Tutoring** - Provide tutoring services for students in subjects you excel in. Websites like Wyzant or Tutor.com can connect you with clients, or you can advertise locally.\n\n4. **Pet Sitting/Dog Walking** - If you love animals, consider pet sitting or dog walking. Rover and Wag are popular platforms for finding gigs.\n\n5. **House Cleaning** - Offer cleaning services through platforms like TaskRabbit, Handy, or local classifieds. Many people need help with cleaning and organizing their homes.\n\n6. **Handyman Services** - If you\u2019re good with repairs and maintenance, you can earn extra money by offering handyman services via TaskRabbit or Thumbtack.\n\n7. **Babysitting** - Look after children during weekends through sites like Care.com or by offering your services within your community.\n\n8. **Event Staff** - Work at events like weddings, parties, or corporate gatherings as a server, bartender, or setup/cleanup crew. Look for opportunities on Indeed or local event staffing agencies.\n\n9. **Photography** - If you have a talent for photography, offer your services for events, portraits, or sell your photos through stock photography websites.\n\n10. **Freelance Writing/Blogging** - Write articles, blog posts, or content for websites. You can find writing gigs on ProBlogger or by pitching to various publications.\n\n11. **Selling Handmade Goods** - Craft your own products and sell them on Etsy, at local markets, or via social media.\n\n12. **Online Surveys/Focus Groups** - Participate in online surveys or focus groups for companies like Swagbucks or Survey Junkie. While not highly lucrative, these can be done in your spare time.\n\n13. **Fitness Instructor** - If you are qualified, you can teach weekend fitness classes, yoga, or personal training sessions.\n\n14. **Virtual Assistant** - Provide administrative support remotely for businesses or entrepreneurs. Platforms like Belay or Fancy Hands can help you find such opportunities.\n\n15. **Gardening/Lawn Care** - Offer services like mowing lawns, landscaping, or gardening in your neighborhood.\n\n16. **Selling Items Online** - Sell unused items on eBay, Poshmark, Mercari, or Craigslist. You can also try flipping items you buy at garage sales or thrift stores.\n\nChoose a side job that aligns with your skills and interests, and make sure it fits your schedule to balance your primary commitments and weekend activities.",
